modules.description: Handles packet transmission and reception on virtual network interfaces, supporting both layer 3 (TUN) and layer 2 (TAP) operations. Works with raw byte buffers and network packets, enabling direct interaction with kernel-level networking stacks. Used for creating virtual private networks, network testing, and packet manipulation in low-level network applications.

Provides functions to create and manage TUN and TAP virtual network interfaces, including setting IP addresses, retrieving MAC addresses and MTU values, and querying interface configurations. Works with Unix file descriptors, interface names, MAC addresses, and IPv4/IPv6 prefixes. Used to configure virtual networks, assign IP addresses dynamically, and inspect interface properties for network simulation or tunneling applications.
